The paper deals with the generation of random strings, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The construction of pairwise independent strings involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of randomness and independence also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-fields of cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the construction of random strings could also be relevant to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
